In large nonstick fry pan coated with cooking spray, cook and stir steak strips over medium-high heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until hot. Remove from fry pan. Add oil to fry pan. Add vegetables. Cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until crisp-tender. Stir in steak strips. Remove from heat. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Spoon onto tortillas. Wrap up. Serve immediately with salsa, sour cream and/or cheese.